squo;t subject to any immigration restriction </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>If your child is looked after by a local council</h3>\n\n<p>They got a <abbr title=\"Child Trust Fund\">CTF</abbr> account if both the following apply:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>they were looked after by a local council before 3 April 2011</li>\n  <li>they meet the other qualifying conditions above (excluding child benefit)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>If you work overseas and get a European family benefit</h3>\n\n<p>Your child got a <abbr title=\"Child Trust Fund\">CTF</abbr> account if all of the following apply:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>they were born between 1 September 2002 and 2 January 2011</li>\n  <li>your child lives in the UK</li>\n  <li>you were paid a family benefit by another European Union country for at least one day before 4 January 2011</li>\n  <li>you work in that same country</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>How it works</h2>\n\n<p>You can add up to £3,600 a year to the account. The money belongs to the child but can&rsquo;t be taken out until they&rsquo;re 18.</p>\n\n<p>You could get extra money paid directly into the account - if you&rsquo;re on a low income, for example.</p>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s no tax to pay on the <abbr title=\"Child Trust Fund\">CTF</abbr> income or any profits it makes. It won&rsquo;t affect any benefits or tax credits you receive.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If your child isn’t eligible for a <abbr title=\"Child Trust Fund\">CTF</abbr> account, you may be able to open a <a href=\"/junior-individual-savings-accounts/overview\" title=\"Junior Individual Savings Accounts (ISA)\">Junior ISA</a> instead.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/child-trust-funds/child-trust-fund-vouchers","slug":"child-trust-fund-vouchers","order":2,"title":"Child Trust Fund vouchers","body":"<p>Vouchers worth £250 or £50, depending on when your child became entitled, were issued to Child Benefit claimants to open an account.</p>\n\n<p>The voucher was sent to the person who gets 